      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">A <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=R1">Ramadan</ref> drummer beats his <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=D2">davul</ref> in a cobbled lane in front of a house door, looking into the camera. Two boys peep over his large drum. To his right, two men wearing long dark coats, leather boots and official hats, are standing at a door. A third boy standing between them is placing something onto a little plate that one of them is holding. The other smiles into the camera.</ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet" subtype="comment">Photographs of <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=R1">Ramadan</ref> musicians were often printed on the first day of <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=R1">Ramadan</ref> celebrations.</ab>
